        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Rabbi Shimon's Position: Distinguishing by Kedusha Type",
      "display_title": "R. Shimon's Logic",
      "timestamp": "20:19",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Shimon's hermeneutics: 'bein tov u'vein ra' indicates material difference",
          "display_title": "R. Shimon's Read",
          "timestamp": "20:19"
        },
        {
          "title": "This indicates kodshei mizbe'ach where blemish matters",
          "display_title": "Kodshei Mizbe'ach",
          "timestamp": "20:30"
        },
        {
          "title": "Atem excludes bedek habayit from the living requirement",
          "display_title": "Atem Excludes Treasury",
          "timestamp": "20:38"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Meitivei Baraita: Resolving the Interpretations",
      "display_title": "Meitivei Baraita",
      "timestamp": "22:52",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Baraita: unblemished buried, blemished redeemed for korbanot",
          "display_title": "Temimim & Mumim",
          "timestamp": "22:52"
        },
        {
          "title": "Initial assumption: this works for Reish Lakish if blemish came later",
          "display_title": "First Assumption",
          "timestamp": "27:18"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yochanan's correction: blemish must have existed from start",
          "display_title": "Ba'al Mum Me'ikaro",
          "timestamp": "28:47"
        },
        {
          "title": "Why this interpretation aligns with both Tanna Kamma and Rabbi Shimon",
          "display_title": "Alignment",
          "timestamp": "29:02"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Reish Lakish's Alternative Text and the Shitur Problem",
      "display_title": "Alt. Text & Shitur",
      "timestamp": "32:25",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Reish Lakish's different girsa: more ambiguous about Rabbi Shimon's position",
          "display_title": "Reish Lakish Girsa",
          "timestamp": "32:25"
        },
        {
          "title": "Reconciling with Rabbi Shimon: why doesn't he disagree with Tanna Kamma",
          "display_title": "Reconciliation",
          "timestamp": "32:25"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Question of Redeeming Dead Korbanot and Dog Food",
      "display_title": "Dead Korbanot Issue",
      "timestamp": "33:39",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Yirmiyah's challenge: Reish Lakish allows redeeming dead korbanot",
          "display_title": "Rav Yirmiyah Query",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "How do you avoid the problem of feeding sanctified meat to dogs",
          "display_title": "Keluvim Problem",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Response: only if the animal was shechted improperly beforehand",
          "display_title": "Shechut Chutz Case",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Baraita on Blemished Korbanot and Redemption",
      "display_title": "Blemished Korban Baraita",
      "timestamp": "33:39",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "All halachot of a korban sanctified with ba'al mum me'ikaro",
          "display_title": "Ba'al Mum Laws",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Firstborn, matanot, shearing, work, offspring, milk all permitted",
          "display_title": "Permissibility Details",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "No temura; if dies, can be redeemed (ve'im meisu yipadu)",
          "display_title": "Temura & Redemption",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Dispute: Whose Position Is the Baraita Representing",
      "display_title": "Attribution Dispute",
      "timestamp": "33:39",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Yehuda: this is Rabbi Shimon's position, not Tanna Kamma",
          "display_title": "Rav Yehuda's Claim",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Challenge: why not attribute to both Rabbi Shimon and his opponent",
          "display_title": "Attribution Challenge",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Resolution: we hold like Reish Lakish that Tanna Kamma allows redeeming dead korbanot",
          "display_title": "Reish Lakish Reasoning",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Therefore attribution only to Rabbi Shimon makes sense given the Tanna Kamma interpretation",
          "display_title": "Tanna Kamma Assumption",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Unblemished Problem: Rabbinic Restrictions on Redemption",
      "display_title": "Temimim Restriction",
      "timestamp": "33:39",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Why does baraita forbid redeeming unblemished animals even for treasury",
          "display_title": "Unblemished Burial",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Reason: animals suitable for the altar must never leave the altar's domain",
          "display_title": "Mizbe'ach Domain",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Baraita: one who sanctifies unblemished for treasury must sell to korban buyer",
          "display_title": "Treasury to Korban",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "All suitable for altar never completely leave the altar's jurisdiction",
          "display_title": "Perpetual Claim",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Final Resolution: Distinguishing Positions on Ba'al Mum Me'ikaro",
      "display_title": "Final Resolution",
      "timestamp": "33:39",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Pappa challenges assumption that all agree ba'al mum me'ikaro can be redeemed",
          "display_title": "Challenge",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Mishna lists laws specific to ba'al mum me'ikaro sanctified as korban",
          "display_title": "Mishna Evidence",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Yehuda: only Rabbi Shimon agrees ba'al mum me'ikaro can be redeemed if dead",
          "display_title": "R. Shimon Only",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chachamim (even Tanna Kamma) require living animal even for ba'al mum me'ikaro",
          "display_title": "Chachamim Stringency",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Clarification: refers to extreme view of Tanna d'bei Levi, not normative Tanna Kamma",
          "display_title": "Tanna d'bei Levi",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        },
        {
          "title": "Resolution: we hold Rav like Rabbi Yochanan; Tanna Kamma agrees ba'al mum me'ikaro redeemable",
          "display_title": "Final Agreement",
          "timestamp": "33:39"
        }
      ]
    }
